  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will evaluate the efficacy and safety of two trough-ranges of everolimus given as
      adjunctive therapy in patients with tuberous sclerosis complex (TSC) who have refractory
      partial-onset seizures.

      The study consists of 4 phases for each patient [Baseline phase: From Screening Week -8 (V1)
      to randomization visit at Week 0 (V2)], Core phase, from randomization at Week 0 (V2) to Week
      18 (V11)], Extension phase from Week 18 (V11) until 48 weeks after the last patient has
      completed the core phase, and Post Extension Phase.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
